data.description: Property 146 Alexander Way, located in the desirable city of Richmond Hill, Georgia, is a stunning single-family home that was built in 2006. This charming residence offers a comfortable and spacious living environment, with an impressive finished area of 1,307 square feet. The property sits on a generous lot size of 7,405 square feet that includes a fence, providing ample outdoor space for various recreational activities.Upon entering this delightful home, you are greeted by a warm and inviting atmosphere. The interior features a well-designed floor plan that maximizes the available space, allowing for seamless flow and easy navigation between rooms. The carefully chosen color palette and tasteful finishes create a visually appealing aesthetic throughout.The property boasts two bathrooms, which are thoughtfully designed and equipped with modern fixtures and amenities. These bathrooms offer convenience and functionality, ensuring the needs of the occupants are met. Whether it's a quick morning shower or a relaxing soak in the tub, these bathrooms provide the perfect space to unwind and rejuvenate.The kitchen is a highlight of the home, featuring contemporary cabinetry, ample storage space, and high-quality updated appliances. This well-appointed culinary space encourages the creation of delicious meals and provides an ideal setting for entertaining guests. The adjacent dining area is spacious and can comfortably accommodate a large dining table, perfect for hosting memorable gatherings and dinner parties.The bedrooms in this property are cozy and comfortable, offering a peaceful retreat after a long day. These private spaces provide ample room for relaxation and rest, with large windows that allow natural light to fill the rooms, creating a bright and airy ambiance. The closets in the bedrooms provide ample storage, ensuring that belongings can be kept organized and out of sight.The exterior of this home is equally as impressive, with a well-maintained yard and landscaping that adds to its overall curb appeal. The large lot size offers endless possibilities for outdoor activities, such as gardening, barbecues, or simply enjoying the fresh air. The property also features a driveway and a garage, providing convenient parking for vehicles and additional storage space.Located in the vibrant city of Richmond Hill, this property offers easy access to a wide range of amenities and attractions. Residents can enjoy a variety of shopping and dining options, as well as numerous parks and recreational facilities. The neighborhood is known for its friendly atmosphere and strong sense of community, making it an ideal place to call home.In summary, property 146 Alexander Way is a beautiful single-family home in Richmond Hill, GA, built in 2006. This well-maintained residence offers two bathrooms, a spacious finished area of 1,307 square feet, and a generous lot size of 7,405 square feet. With its inviting interior, well-designed floor plan, and convenient location, this property provides an excellent opportunity for comfortable and enjoyable living.
